The people - Langland's " folk ' and Gaunt'S  knoves'- were villeins still tied to the feudal obligations of work or villeins who had bought their release, free labourers who worked for the highest bidders, free yeomen who had prospeced enough to beoomg successtul farmers, the artisans, craftsmen, joureymen and small tradesmen of the towns, and the retainers and men-at-arms in the pay of landed Lords.